In a petition under this subtitle, a local department may ask the court to find that reasonable efforts to reunify a child with the child's parent or guardian are not required if the local department concludes that a parent or guardian has:
Subjected the child to:
Chronic abuse;
Chronic and life-threatening neglect;
Sexual abuse; or
Torture;
Been convicted, in any state or any court of the United States, of:
A crime of violence against:
A minor offspring of the parent or guardian;
The child; or
Another parent or guardian of the child; or
Aiding or abetting, conspiring, or soliciting to commit a crime described in subitem (i) of this item; or
Involuntarily lost parental rights of a sibling of a child.
